ASABA – A 32-year-old male teacher of the Royal Children School, Asaba, Delta state identified as Emmanuel Okafor has been arrested for allegedly defiling a six-year-old girl. Daily Independent gathered that the incident occurred during school hours on Tuesday, March 1, 2022. A relative of the victim revealed that the 32-year-old teacher refilled the minor inside the school toilet. APC Suffers Mass Defection Of Leaders, Members To PDP In Delta Suspected ‘Yahoo Boys’ Crush Two To Death With SUV… She mentioned that the yet-to-be-named teacher at Royal Children International School in Asaba, Delta state, s3xually molested her niece and left her “badly injured and scattered down there”. According to our source, ” At the police station, the child pointed accusing fingers at the teacher and narrated how it all started”. It was also learnt that a nurse at the Asaba Specialist Hospital confirmed that there was forceful penetration of the minor. However, in a statement issued by the management of the school, they described the incident as false and misleading the allegations levelled against the school and the teacher. The statement stated that “ the school has a proven track record of excellence and would work with relevant authorities to get to the root of the matter. POLL When contacted Police Public Relation Officer (PPRO), DSP Bright Edafe confirmed the arrest of the 32-year-old teacher, Emmanuel Okafor. ” The suspect we have in our custody is 32 year old, Emmanuel Okafor” he stated.